# Defining Lessons


#### Lesson 4 and 5 help students use data to understand their users to gain insight of their needs. 

---


## Lesson 4: Data Visualization

<img src="https://images.code.org/89ffb338a4a8017f4bf7f4bb2780dc9a-image-1714665228682.png" alt="farmwise robot and crops" width="250px"  style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 20px 10px 40px;">

#### In this lesson, students learn to **translate user data** into actionable insights through **visual representations**. 

#### Using examples like robotic vacuum cleaners, students explore how data visualizations can highlight user concerns and inform feature development. 

#### Activities guide them through **creating and interpreting their own visualizations** using tools like Google Sheets, giving them a deep understanding of how visual data can reveal trends and needs within a community.

