## Lesson 5: User Stories and Problem Statements
<img src="https://images.code.org/28033debc5875a22c7dba89f17cb098e-image-1714665959027.png" alt="bar graph" width="250px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 30px 40px 40px;">

#### This lesson teaches students to understand user needs and articulate problem statements by constructing user stories from data to insightfully address real concerns.

#### Activities will challenge students to **analyze user behavior patterns** and to think critically about the underlying reasons for these behaviors, using iterative questioning to refine their understanding.

#### By the end of the lesson, students should be able to create **user stories and corresponding problem statements** that guide the development of user-centered solutions.

